      "source": [
        "# Value-at-Risk & Expected Shortfall Engine\n",
        "### Portfolio Value-at-Risk and Expected Shortfall Measurement System\n",
        "\n",
        "**Author:** Quant Risk Engineering Project\n",
        "**Purpose:** Compute, compare, and backtest Value-at-Risk (VaR) and Expected Shortfall (ES / CVaR)\n",
        "for a multi-asset portfolio using three industry-standard methodologies:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Historical Simulation VaR/ES**\n",
        "2. **Parametric (Variance-Covariance) VaR/ES**\n",
        "3. **Monte Carlo Simulation VaR/ES**\n",
        "\n",
        "The engine also includes a **Kupiec Proportion-of-Failures backtest** to statistically validate\n",
        "model accuracy, mirroring how bank market-risk departments validate VaR models under Basel/FRTB.\n",
        "\n",
        "> Run cells top to bottom. No local installation needed — this notebook is self-contained for Google Colab.\n"
      ],
      "id": "ZsY5O-qnOXRJ"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rb7bgQ_tOXRN"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Setup & Installation"
      ],
      "id": "rb7bgQ_tOXRN"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G1i-Lvx-OXRO"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# ==============================================================\n",
        "# CELL 1: INSTALL & IMPORT DEPENDENCIES\n",
        "# ==============================================================\n",
        "# Colab ships with most scientific packages pre-installed; we only\n",
        "# need to ensure yfinance is present for market data retrieval.\n",
        "\n",
        "!pip install -q yfinance --upgrade\n",
        "\n",
        "import warnings\n",
        "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import matplotlib.dates as mdates\n",
        "from scipy import stats\n",
        "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n",
        "from typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Optional\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reproducibility for Monte Carlo simulation\n",
        "RANDOM_SEED = 42\n",
        "np.random.seed(RANDOM_SEED)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Consistent, professional plotting style\n",
        "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
        "    \"figure.figsize\": (11, 6),\n",
        "    \"figure.dpi\": 110,\n",
        "    \"axes.grid\": True,\n",
        "    \"grid.alpha\": 0.3,\n",
        "    \"axes.spines.top\": False,\n",
        "    \"axes.spines.right\": False,\n",
        "    \"font.size\": 11,\n",
        "    \"axes.titlesize\": 13,\n",
        "    \"axes.titleweight\": \"bold\",\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Environment ready.\")\n",
        "print(f\"Python: {sys.version.split()[0]} | NumPy: {np.__version__} | Pandas: {pd.__version__}\")\n"
      ],
      "id": "G1i-Lvx-OXRO"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
