        "id": "nQOb777lOXRY"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 9. Notes, Limitations & Suggested Upgrades\n",
        "\n",
        "**Limitations of this implementation:**\n",
        "- Historical Simulation assumes the future resembles the sampled historical window and gives no weight to recency.\n",
        "- Parametric VaR assumes normally distributed returns, which understates tail risk (fat tails / negative skew are common in equities).\n",
        "- Monte Carlo here uses a multivariate normal — it does not capture volatility clustering or non-normal joint tail dependence (copulas would address this).\n",
        "- Portfolio weights are treated as static; no rebalancing or intraday exposure changes are modeled.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Potential Upgrades:**\n",
        "- Add **EWMA (RiskMetrics)** or **GARCH(1,1)** volatility forecasting for time-varying VaR.\n",
        "- Replace the multivariate normal in Monte Carlo with a **Student-t copula** to capture fat tails and tail dependence.\n",
        "- Add **Cornish-Fisher VaR** to adjust parametric VaR for skewness and kurtosis.\n",
        "- Extend to **Component VaR / Incremental VaR** to attribute risk to individual positions.\n",
        "- Add a **Christoffersen independence test** alongside Kupiec to check for breach clustering.\n",
        "- Wrap the dashboard in `ipywidgets` for interactive parameter adjustment inside Colab.\n"
      ],
      "id": "nQOb777lOXRY"
    }
